==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Analcime
<hw>A*nal"cime</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'an</grk> priv. + <grk>'a`lkimos</grk> strong, <grk>'alkh`</grk>
strength: cf. F. <ets>analcime</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A
white or flesh-red mineral, of the zeolite family, occurring in
isometric crystals. By friction, it acquires <xex>a weak</xex>
electricity; hence its name.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Analcite</ent>⟦br⟧
